It's time to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where only a bit of decorating has been done and nothing else.
The awful electric fireplace and the hearth must go. We need to encase the chimney, replace and smooth out the crumbling plaster, and then build the wardrobe to measure.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the work is done.
At the back of the chimney, we found a few dried-out dead birds, very desiccated :(.
Everything ready for the plumber next week
The small side niche has turned out well
A new wardrobe will fit here (but we haven't even started on the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look at what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought to install this nice little vent flap so that the fireplace doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the cap and hood. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there🪺
The plasterer is done. The flooring will be laid tomorrow!
The cork underlay is laid, I have built a toilet paper roll dust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
The floor parts are ready and can be laid. We're having tea break right now
Buhu. Today we're progressing slowly because of super complicated cuts around the door posts so we have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be newly laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Fertig, aber am Ende! Die Krönung war die fürchterliche Montageanleitung für das neue Bett. Heute Nacht werden wir gut schlafen!
Es fehlen noch der Boden im Flur und alle Sockelleisten. Der Dekorateur kommt in einem Monat, also haben wir momentan Rohputz-Schick.
Noch etwas Heimwerkerarbeit am Abend, um die unteren Abschnitte um die Türpfosten auszusägen oder zu meißeln, wo der Fußboden dann nahtlos drunter passen soll.
Die Korkunterlage liegt jetzt auch im Flur.
Gestern sind wir mit dem Boden im Flur fertig geworden! Dann um 5 Uhr früh raus, um Gegenstand 1 in Heathrow abzuholen, dann ein Nickerchen und Endspurt im Flur, die Leisten sind angebracht. Fugen werden gemacht, wenn der Kleber trocken ist
